      <description>&lt;p&gt;I recently joined &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.wikifolio.com&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;wikifolio&lt;/a&gt; as Head of Business Intelligence and Data Science.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I also just graduated from the &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.vgsf.ac.at/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Vienna Graduate School of Finance&lt;/a&gt; where my research focused on the economics of technological innovations in the financial sector. One of my papers shows how blockchain-based settlement introduces limits to arbitrage in cross-market trading. In another paper, I analyze how consumers react to the introduction of overdraft facilities through a mobile banking app. In my solo-authored paper, I investigate the potential of crowdfunding mechanisms to elicit demand information and improve the screening of viable projects under different valuation structures.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Before starting my PhD studies, I was a research assistant in the field of labor economics at the &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.ihs.ac.at/de/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Institute for Advanced Studies&lt;/a&gt; and an intern at &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.ithubacapital.com/home.html&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Ithuba Capital&lt;/a&gt; and the Austrian &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.fma.gv.at/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Financial Market Authority&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
